1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He'll drink a couple of extra cups of coffee, maybe cruise around the neighborhood a while,

2
00:00:01,615 --> 00:00:05,505
or do a dozen little things to postpone that first call.

3
00:00:06,175 --> 00:00:08,544
I train each new man this way.

4
00:00:08,655 --> 00:00:12,465
I explain to him that the only way to start is to start.

5
00:00:12,574 --> 00:00:13,905
Don't deliberate.

6
00:00:14,015 --> 00:00:16,064
Don't postpone getting started.

7
00:00:16,175 --> 00:00:16,945
Do this.

8
00:00:17,054 --> 00:00:22,225
Just park your car, get your sample case, walk to the door, ring the bell,

9
00:00:22,495 --> 00:00:29,344
smile, say good morning, and make your presentation, all mechanically, without a lot of conscious thought.

10
00:00:29,775 --> 00:00:32,945
Start making calls this way and you break the ice.

11
00:00:33,135 --> 00:00:38,785
By the second or third call, your mind is sharp and your presentations become effective.

12
00:00:39,294 --> 00:00:45,905
A humorist once said the most difficult problem in life was getting out of a warm bed into a cold room,

13
00:00:46,015 --> 00:00:47,264
and he had a point.

14
00:00:47,535 --> 00:00:53,905
The longer you lie there and think how unpleasant it will be to get up, the more difficult it becomes.

15
00:00:54,175 --> 00:01:01,745
Even in such a simple operation as this, mechanical action, just throwing off the covers and putting your feet on the floor,

16
00:01:01,855 --> 00:01:03,265
defeats dread.

17
00:01:03,935 --> 00:01:05,344
The point is clear.

18
00:01:05,615 --> 00:01:10,544
People who get things done in this world don't wait for the spirit to move them.

19
00:01:10,735 --> 00:01:12,465
They move the spirit.

20
00:01:12,975 --> 00:01:14,864
Try these two exercises.

21
00:01:14,864 --> 00:01:16,625
1.

22
00:01:17,135 --> 00:01:23,985
Use the mechanical way to accomplish simple but sometimes unpleasant business and household chores.

23
00:01:24,255 --> 00:01:31,584
Rather than think about the unpleasant features of the task, jump right in and get going without a lot of deliberation.

24
00:01:33,294 --> 00:01:38,705
Perhaps the most unpleasant household task to most women is washing dishes.

25
00:01:38,895 --> 00:01:40,785
My mother is no exception.

26
00:01:41,054 --> 00:01:46,145
But she has mastered a mechanical approach to dispensing with this task quickly,

27
00:01:46,175 --> 00:01:48,945
so she can return to things she likes to do.

28
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:56,705
As she leaves the table, she always mechanically picks up several dishes, and without thinking about the task ahead,

29
00:01:56,895 --> 00:01:58,225
just gets started.

30
00:01:58,415 --> 00:02:00,705
In just a few minutes, she is through.

31
00:02:00,975 --> 00:02:05,745
Doesn't this beat stacking dishes and dreading the unpleasant inevitable?

32
00:02:06,255 --> 00:02:07,584
Do this today.

33
00:02:07,775 --> 00:02:10,544
Pick the one thing you like to do least.

34
00:02:10,655 --> 00:02:15,665
Then, without letting yourself deliberate on or dread the task, do it.

35
00:02:15,935 --> 00:02:19,025
That's the most efficient way to handle chores.

36
00:02:22,015 --> 00:02:28,465
Next, use the mechanical way to create ideas, map out plans, solve problems,
